  <ParaLine 
   <String `This document outlines the '>
  >
  <ParaLine 
   <String `plans for WriterStation for 1995'>
  >
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 286325>
  <PgfTag `FirstBody'>
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 24>
   <String `This document outlines marketing requirements for the WriterStation product suite dur'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  >
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ing 1995'>
  >
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 286342>
  <PgfTag `Body'>
  <ParaLine 
   <String `The goals for 1995:'>
  >
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 287663>
  <PgfTag `Bullet'>
  <PgfNumString `\xa5 \t'>
  <ParaLine 
   <String `asdfl;kj asdf;lkj asdl;kfj asdl;kfj as;lkdfj l;aksdjf l;kasjdf l;kasjdf l;kajs flkjasdf '>
  >
  <ParaLine 
   <String `asfdlkj sdflkj sdflkj lkj lkj lkj sdflkj sdflkjs dflkjs dflkj sdflkj sdflkj sdflkjsd flkjsdflk '>
  >
  <ParaLine 
   <String `jsdflkj sdflkj sdflkjs dflkjs dflkjs dflkjs dflkjs dflkj sdflkj sdflkj sdlfkj sdflkjs df'>
  >
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 287216>
  <PgfTag `Bullet'>
  <PgfNumString `\xa5 \t'>
  <ParaLine 
   <String `asdf;lkjasdf;lkj asdf;lkj asdf;lkjas df;lkjas df;lkjasd f;lkjasd f;lkjasdf ;lkajsdf ;lka.'>
  >
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 288228>
  <PgfTag `1Heading'>
  <PgfNumString `1.0\t'>
  <ParaLine 
   <String `TOC'>
  >
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 288229>
  <PgfTag `2Heading'>
  <PgfNumString `\t1.1\t'>
  <ParaLine 
   <String `daf;lkjasdf;lkjasfdl;kjasdf'>
  >
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 281683>
  <PgfTag `1Heading'>
  <PgfNumString `2.0\t'>
  <ParaLine 
   <Marker 
    <MType 9>
    <MText `22863: 1Heading: 1.0 Introduction'>
    <MCurrPage `1'>
    <Unique 287703>
   > # end of Marker
   <String `Introduction'>
  >
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 286785>
  <PgfTag `FirstBody'>
  <ParaLine 
   <String `WriterStation was first sold by Datalogics in the mid 1980\xd5 s. It was designed for the '>
  >
  <ParaLine 
   <String `IBM PC running under MS-DOS in character mode. WriterStation was then ported to '>
  >
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the Presentation Manager under OS/2 and expanded to use multiple fonts and adjustable '>
  >
  <ParaLine 
   <String `character width.'>
  >
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 286786>
  <PgfTag `Body'>
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Originally designed for DL Pager-like markup, WriterStation was converted to direct '>
  >
  <ParaLine 
   <String `SGML compliance very early in its life. Its designers assisted with the creation of the '>
  >
  <ParaLine 
   <String `SGML standard. '>
  >
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 286794>
  <PgfTag `Body'>
  <ParaLine 
   <String `A project is currently underway to finish porting WriterStation to Windows. '>
  >
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 281686>
  <PgfTag `1Heading'>
  <PgfNumString `3.0\t'>
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 25>
   <String `Test some specialized features of FrameMaker'>
  >
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 285355>
  <PgfTag `2Heading'>
  <PgfNumString `\t3.1\t'>
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Cross-Reference'>
  >
 > # end of Para
 <Para 
  <Unique 287537>
  <PgfTag `FirstBody'>
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Here is an xref. \>'>
   <XRef 
    <XRefName `See Heading & Page'>
    <XRefSrcText `22863: 1Heading: 1.0 Introduction'>
    <XRefSrcIsElem No>
    <XRefSrcFile `'>
    <XRefLastUpdate  800716890 720000>
    <Unique 287706>
   > # end of XRef
   <String `See \xd2 '>
   <String `Introduction'>
   <String `\xd3  on page'>
   <Char HardSpace>
   <String `1.'>
   <XRefEnd >
